ce:section.ce:para:
This study shows that Fe3+ ions are detected at low concentrations and is a good indicator of the lower Fe3+ ions. We compared the detecting efficiency of this Fe3+ sensor with the other observed CQDs based Fe3+ sensors (see Table 1
                           ) and also compared the performance of the proposed method with some existing traditional detection methods without using CQDs in terms of linear range, limit of detection, R
                           2 value, response time and detection of materials (see Table 2
                           ). The CQD also behaves as a fluorescent probe for the sensitive and selective detection for Fe3+ ions. It is realized that only Fe3+ made a significant feedback from all the confirmed metal ions, and other metal ions no longer had a further impact, suggesting that our proposed CQDs were successfully used to detect the Fe3+ ions as the sensing platform.
